The course includes lectures (acute sports injuries, overuse syndromes, tendinopathies, rehabiliatation of sports injuries) and seminars (case analysis, rehabilitation of sports injuries).
All recorded e-lectures can be viewed in the Moodle environment any time.  One work seminar is conducted in web (BBB) and one practical session will be performed as contact lesson.

In order to pass the course:
-  participation in seminar and practical session
-  multiple choice test (Final test in Moodle) according to e-lectures' materialsObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course to give principal knowledges in sports traumatology and main principles of injury prevention and treatmentLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) is able to give an adequate first aid in case of acute injuries of the athlete 2) is able to evaluate the most common acute injuries of the athlete 3) is able to evaluate the most common musculoskeletal overuse syndromes in athletes 4) is well-acquianted with rehabilitation of sports injuries
